<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-14-0883 </DOCNO><TEXT>Results of systematic study of gamma- and gamma-neutron radiation effect(both during and after gaining certain fluencesand doses) on dielectricand optical characteristics of industrial types of electric ceramic materialswere analyzed for the first time from the view-point of phase materialcomposition. The role of glassy and crystal phases in formation of radiationproperties was clarified. Theoretical aspects of radiation processesin ceramic structures were considered. 146 refs.; 37 figs.</TEXT></DOC>